<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>2 December 2013</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Eifion Edwards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (GMC0010)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">I am not a medical doctor. I write as an individual regards my belief that there is no fair </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">structure</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> at the GMC </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">for anyone</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">, so that a claim to fairness by the GMC tends to be ‘just what is said on paper’, the reality is different. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34pt; padding-left:2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">For years I have said that poor attitudes (bullying) at a nearby NHS (not my local NHS) will “cause death” (quote from my 2004 letter). Death rates were focused on in the media by 2008. I felt and still feel totally unable to report any doctor to the GMC (including a Medical Director and Clinical Director) as I feel the GMC cannot be trusted at all. Both of those doctors left that NHS. A Stafford style review starts on limited aspects in 2014</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34pt; padding-left:2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">I have taught management at University. It occurs to me that the GMC has a problem with it’s very structure. I ask you ignore the hype by the GMC. The GMC is “structured” to protect, promote and maintain the networks of many local NHS managers who often cause the most harm to the public.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Whereas </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Regulators are to ensure that their chief officers, leaders, staff and agents must act with the same standards that the regulator tries to bring to a profession, trade or business</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The reality may be that a commitment to standards and integrity does not occur at the GMC, where the evidence of inappropriate behaviour at the GMC, may be the GMC’s choice of a main structure that is so obviously lacking in adequate fairness.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.33pt; padding-left:2.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A close analysis can suggest the structure, strategy and functioning of the GMC is around the GMC’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">raison </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">d’etre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">impose the will of management</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and on the basis that local NHS and GMC management </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">can do no wrong</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and are to be totally unaccountable. Yet from the local NHS scandals we know that local management can often be the problem. And a very serious problem. It follows that the GMC with foresight of what can occur, still imposes the flawed GMC structure and the flawed GMC ways of working, that are expected to cause suffering and death across the UK. I believe the harm that GMC knowingly imposes is evidence that neither I, nor any other can trust the GMC.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.67pt; padding-left:3.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It also follows that the GMC structure, strategy and functioning is ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">conflicting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’ with and is ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">incompatible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’ with the Intention of Parliament and Parliament’s legislation on whistle blowing, protecting the public, human rights and very much more.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The media over the years tells us of a history of the GMC as not being fair or credible in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> responses to the public when doctors do the most serious wrongs. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Now, the NHS is substantially more complex. As one example there is the question of abuse of power in NHS zero tolerance by doctors. But when making a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">complaint about the doctor places the matter at the GMC, it is the GMC who may abusing their power, to even without consent, the GMC may write inaccurate material where there is no accountability and no process to challenge or change the untrue material when the GMC writes to harm members of the public. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30pt; padding-left:6pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">To consider the accountability of the GMC, we need to think of what can go wrong. It appears to me that there is no accountability if the GMC were to endorse that doctors should do some of most serious wrongs in UK law. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.67pt; padding-left:5.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If some police can act as in ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">plebgate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, it follows there is hypothetically a potential that doctors and even some at the GMC can also potentially veer towards acting like ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">plebgate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">when controlling police to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">cover up</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> local NHS failures.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A different quite chilling modern NHS issue is the use and abuse of Public Protection measures where doctors’ subjective views “predict risk” potentially posed by individuals, who have not yet committed the offence – and even not committed any criminal offence. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.33pt; padding-left:2.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Public protection (MAPPA - Multi Agency Public Protection arrangements) has the rules that accountability is by each member of the public protection committee, being referred to their professional body, - I.E. Doctors involved in public protection are reported to the GMC. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">MAPPA rules can mean the head of each public service must be involved. So we are back to the public reporting local management doctors to the GMC, where the GMC is structured that local mangers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">can do no wrong</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It follows there needs to be accountability to deal with to what extent the GMC colludes with local management doctors to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">cover up</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> NHS failures, to use even </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">entirely bogus public protection papers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to try cause indefinite loss of liberty. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I would like the committee to follow up my suspicion that an inappropriate culture at the GMC is at least part cause in the 100 suicides of doctors being investigated by the GMC. I do not argue around the original charge the doctors face, but that the doctors would be overwhelmed by how totally inconsistent the conduct of GMC staff can be. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.67pt; padding-left:3.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">From the evidence I have or have seen I believe the culture of the GMC being of the worse, if not worst kind of unaccountable mischief. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.67pt; padding-left:1.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I believe even revalidation in the hands of the GMC may too easily be just another tool for workplace bullying and preventing whistle blowing. So that GMC statutory powers need to be urgently passed to a parent body that commissions ‘fitness to practice’ and ‘revalidation’ to various more appropriate impartial bodies.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34pt; padding-left:2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Regards Human Rights it is the duty of Parliament to ensure that the use of the power of the state over the individual is used proportionately and not abused. Presently there are no ways to protect the public from the GMC. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.67pt; padding-left:3.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I believe it is not possible for Parliament to provide accountability to protect the pub</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ic and medical profession from the GMC without removing the statutory powers of the to a parent body who can commission back regulation and ensure accountability if needed on a daily basis.    </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Contents</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The GMC structure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (both the legal structure and the organisational structure) is based on the Medical Director as the “Responsible Officer” making the decisions on fitness to practice (and revalidation) for that NHS region. But as scandals are often caused by local </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">cover ups</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, it is quite foreseeable that the GMC imposing the will of local management as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">can do no wrong,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (when local management can too often be the cause of the more serious problems) means the GMC imposes exceptional problems, suffering and deaths on the UK. The GMC structure is not adequately fair. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Financial and Legal Services, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">unlike the GMC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have split up what they do into more than one regulatory body, and they employed mostly new leaders, managers, lawyers and decision makers, to create a needed culture change.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Accountability: But what can go wrong?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> To scrutinise accountability we need at least some hypothetical examples that are adequately in tune with what really goes on at the GMC. Can we imagine how bad mischief by the GMC ever be? Is it too </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">far fetched</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the GMC colludes with the GMC’s local Medical or Clinical Directors who entirely make up a man has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> ‘significant irreversible brain damage’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, leaving the public and profession in despair at the ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">sins against the profession’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and a GMC culture that can inflict exceptional harm on the public? Is there indication of the GMC’s inappropriate culture, that if it exists, is a part cause of around 100 doctors committing suicide while under scrutiny by the GMC? </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">GMC Lawyers: Who controls the GMC? Who is unaccountable? </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Much of the GMC is controlled by lawyers. The senior managers also tend to be lawyers. Accountability for the GMC lawyers is supposed to be via the senior lawyers at the GMC. I have tested the system to find no will and no working procedure to deal with accountability of GMC lawyers. Any claim to accountability will be ‘just what they say on paper’ but not a reality. By copying ways of working from other sectors, accountability occurs if there is a system to prove the reality that procedures are starting to work. Going by standards in other sectors the GMC must prove that they deal with the sort of problems I can raise, to prove accountability is starting to work regards GMC staff.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Informal structures: The GMC culture has a bearing on the effectiveness of a number of main regulators</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. By informal structure we mean, we it is not who is appointed as the boss who influences the most, but personalities and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">relationships that really affect decisions and trends. It is important for the Select Committee to note that the GMC way of doing business controls the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Nursing and Midwifery Council</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Solicitors Regulation Authority</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> because the GMC staff migrate to take over those regulators. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Revalidation in the hands of the GMC can be just another tool for NHS workplace bullies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">that totally prevents whistle blowing.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> How can any doctor whistle blow if the GMC revalidates a doctor by a subjective opinion of whether their boss thinks they cooperate with the will of their management? If the GMC says local management can do no wrong, how can a whistle blowing doctor be expected to say a management level doctor does wrong? </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Main submission.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As we are aware, where the effects of one legislative measure ‘conflicts’ with another. Or is ‘incompatible’ with human rights or the intention of Parliament. Or that Parliament could not have foreseen the effect it’s legislation would have. Then Parliament needs to give consideration to what changes to the conflicting or incompatible legislative measures are needed. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As reported in the media it follows that the GMC has never been out of a cloud of alarming failure, so that I question whether the GMC now tries to draw attention away from such exceptional failure by oppressively flexing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> statutory muscle, to bully even members of the public and the GMC takes little thought for the harm it causes.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The statutory power of the GMC has can conflict with other legislation, or the intentions implicit within that legislation, to protect the safety and human rights of the public and to whistle blow </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">GMC structure is based on conflicts of interest </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Sometimes if the structure of an organisation is skewed dramatically to only accommodate one approach, then no new strategy or public relations assertions, can possibly take the organisation to do anything other than the original structure dictates.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Many do not realise that the major structure of the GMC, (that is both the legal structure and the organisational structure) is almost wholly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dependant</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on the local Medical Director as a Responsible Officer to make decisions or recommendations for the GMC. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The local Medical Director can be responsible for even 1200 doctors and so a Medical Director relies on his Clinical Director or Clinical Leads. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">That can mean that there are many doctors out there that the GMC imposes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">can do no wrong</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘If’ there is a good and able local NHS management, may be things are not so bad. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 48pt; padding-left:6pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">But as we know merely hoping for a good local NHS management is not accountability and is playing Russian Roulette with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">peoples</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> lives because too many local NHS have a conflict of interest that they may wish to:- </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Seek to hide failing regards performance evaluation and targets </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A local NHS tends to avoid admitting their doctors do wrong in case that can make them liable in legal disputes. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 101.33pt; padding-left:6.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Medical managers may simply not want to report a friend or colleague to the GMC. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 101.33pt; padding-left:6.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Medical managers may wish to be more eager to report doctors who have done no wrong but rather, they do not get on with, (bullying).</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Medical managers may want to reports whistle blowers to the GMC The media said one doctor faced around 100 charges at the GMC for trying to whistle blow about standards. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 101.33pt; padding-left:6.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">With the GMC being the stick with which errant medical managers beat whistle blowers and any who wish to draw attention to wrongdoing at the NHS, the GMC is clearly a danger to both the public and good doctors.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Splitting up Regulation in Financial and Legal Services. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There are lessons from the strengths and weakness in the history of failure and changes to Financial Services Authority and Legal Services Regulation. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Problems occurred from a relaxed loose approach of around 2004 in design of Financial Services Regulation so that a revamp followed by the credit crunch in 2008. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 48pt; padding-left:6pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I ask the Select Committee to note the lesson, that now the Financial Services Authority has been split by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Financial Services Act 2012</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> into the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Prudential Regulation Authority</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Financial Conduct Authority. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As we are well aware, so has the Law Society with the Law Society separated from the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Office for the Supervision of Solicitors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (OSS) to become the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Solicitors Regulation Authority</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (SRA) which is under a parent body the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Legal Services Board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which came into being by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Legal Services Act 2007.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I ask the select committee to note that:- </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.33pt; padding-left:6.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Firstly the main changes from OSS to SRA was a change of structure more fit for purpose.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.33pt; padding-left:6.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">But secondly the civil servants behind the 2007 Legal Services Act made sure of a culture change by a process of change, so that not so many decision making leaders or manager from the OSS were to take the SRA forward. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The hidden criteria ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">remain a regulator’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> under the Legal Services Board was a culture cage by new managers at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">al</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> levels of manager from the bottom to the top. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 47.33pt; padding-left:6.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Accountability of legal regulation has the extra stage as the Legal Services Board can strip a regulators like the SRA or Bar Council of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> role without going back for the permission of Parliament. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Accountability in what sort of issues? What can go wrong?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> To scrutinise accountability we need at least some hypothetical examples that are adequately in tune with what really goes on at the GMC. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Can we imagine how bad that misconduct by the GMC ever be? Is it too </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">far fetched</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the GMC colludes with GMC’s local Medical or Clinical Directors who entirely make up a man </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">has significant irreversible brain damage</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, leaving the public and profession in despair at the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">sins against the profession</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and a GMC culture that can inflict exceptional harm to the public? </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What can the Select Committee do to see if inappropriate behaviour by the GMC is a part cause or main cause of around 100 doctors committing suicide while under investigation by the GMC? </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It may be possible to share evidence of how the GMC leaders and staff appear to me to collude in the use of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">actual bogus papers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.   </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Informal structures can mean that the GMC poses a real risk to the effectiveness of a number of main regulators</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As we are aware by informal structure we mean it can be irrelevant who is the boss, but rather which personalities control the decisions and bring influence.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If I am even just partly correct in what I believe regards the GMC being an organisation engulfed in inappropriate behaviour leading to an inappropriate culture from top to bottom, what effect on the UK of GMC staff migrating to other regulators such as the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Nursing and Midwifery Council</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Solicitors Regulation Authority </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are run by GMC staff?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">GMC Lawyers: Who really controls the GMC And who is most unaccountable. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Is the GMC’s Legal Department also over run by a culture of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">cover up</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> what the GMC does wrong? </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I believe GMC Legal (the GMC’s own major legal department) is one of the worst examples of any law firm anywhere. I ask the committee to draw out what accountability could and should exist. . </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Much of the GMC is controlled by lawyers. Most of the key managers are lawyers and. I believe that I witness the GMC lawyers as amongst the most unscrupulous. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Please would the committee press for evidence other GMC about procedures to complain about what the SRA calls someone else’s lawyer (the GMC lawyers) abusing their power. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There are SRA rules regards lawyers (e.g. GMC lawyers) who abuse their power to unrepresented persons where the internal department of the law firm should receive and deal with complaints. I am concerned that the army of GMC lawyers avoid correct procedures for internal accountability </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Revalidation in the hands of the GMC is just another tool for NHS workplace bullies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">that totally prevents whistle blowing.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The GMC revalidation is hinged on, does the doctor get approval to continue as a doctor based on the subjective opinion of his Medical line mangers as passed to their Medical Director that the doctor complies with the will of managers and their (‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">superior?’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) insight.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">GMC revalidation is not about </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> professional subject to by peer review’ but a profession degraded into being employees that are not permitted to express honest and competent professional opinion.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The High Court will almost never interfere with a professional who express and honest and competent opinion. But from what I directly witness the GMC imposes worse standards on the medical profession then would occur if the GMC did not exist. This is because of two situations. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Firstly, a typical doctor will want to do their job honestly and competently. Although there are more ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">top down’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> pressures on doctors than the GMC, I believe the effect from the GMC flexing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> statutory muscle and abuses of revalidation, is that doctors are under the fear of not being revalidated if they do not comply with the mischief of more senior doctors. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Secondly, staff and leaders at the GMC, are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">totally unaccountable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, yet from what I witness they do not behave anywhere near to the same standards that doctors should expect of members of their profession.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><div style="width:auto; height:auto; float:left;"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1</span></p></div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>